comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-06T23:51:07.660Z",codex-agent,"Planning evidence 2026-07-07: all-status duplicate checks showed pm-4k6b is the canonical adaptive context engine parent; no focused child existed for signal extraction, scorer contract, or token-budget packing. Added non-duplicate implementation slices: pm-3hps (derived signal feature store), pm-h3no (pluggable SDK scorer contract), and pm-55ra (diversity-aware token-budget packer). Algorithm sketch: build an index-backed candidate set from focus/claim/query/dependency windows; compute normalized signal vectors for recency, activity density, graph proximity, priority/risk/deadline pressure, semantic similarity, knowledge density, author affinity, and continuity deltas; combine them through a deterministic default scorer with extension override; pack by marginal utility per token while preserving required anchors and degrading projection depth before dropping items; expose score breakdowns for explainability and pm-atfm evaluation.\n"
notes[10]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-07T15:12:12.161Z",maintainer-agent,"Algorithm brainstorm 2026-07-07 (planning pass) — concrete candidate algorithms for the scorer, extending the body's signal list with the combination machinery:\n(1) Scale-free recency via ACT-R base-level activation: activation(i) = ln(sum over accesses t_j of t_j^-d), d~0.5, computed from the item's history stream timestamps. Log-time decay is the one law that behaves identically for a minutes-old scratch workspace and a decades-old archive (the spectrum invariant pm-z436/pm-g2zz demand) and it rewards frequency AND recency in one term, replacing ad-hoc half-life constants.\n(2) Spreading activation for associative recall: seed activation at the focus item, active claims, and current plan step; propagate over typed edges (blocked_by/parent/related plus semantic k-NN edges from the hybrid index) with per-edge-type damping; k iterations of sparse matrix-vector products over the derived read index keeps it O(neighborhood), never O(workspace).\n(3) Learned signal weights with explainability preserved: keep the final score a LINEAR combination of the per-signal contributions (so --explain-ranking stays truthful), but fit the weights per workspace offline against the pm-atfm eval harness as the objective (pairwise learning-to-rank on 'agent actually used this item next' labels derivable from history streams). Weights persist in settings; default weights ship for cold start.\n(4) Token-budget packing as submodular selection: greedy by marginal-value-per-token (MMR-style redundancy penalty so two near-duplicate items do not both spend budget), with per-item projection degradation levels (full body -> summary -> id+title) as fractional knapsack steps. Greedy is provably near-optimal for submodular objectives and is deterministic.\nAll four stay SDK-side behind scoreContextCandidates; none require new stored state beyond what history streams and the read index already hold."
  "2026-07-07T15:26:05.199Z",maintainer-agent,"Algorithm brainstorm 2026-07-07 (planning pass, continuation of (1)-(4)):\n(5) Reciprocal rank fusion as the cold-start combiner: before a workspace has enough history for (3)'s learned linear weights, combining per-signal RANKS instead of scores — score(i) = sum over signals s of 1/(k + rank_s(i)), k~60 — needs no calibration between signals with incompatible scales (activation vs cosine similarity vs priority ordinals), is deterministic, and is robust to any one signal degenerating (a broken/empty signal ranks everything equally and cancels out). Graduation path: ship RRF as the zero-config default, fit (3)'s linear weights per workspace once pm-atfm labels exist, keep RRF as the documented fallback. Explainability holds: per-signal rank contributions are exactly reportable in --explain-ranking.\n(6) Write-time incremental signal maintenance: at millions of items (pm-g2zz) even O(candidates) re-scoring at read time is dominated by recomputing per-item activation/affinity from raw history streams. Because every mutation already lands one immutable history entry, fold signal state incrementally at write time: each history append updates that item's running activation term, author-affinity counters, and semantic-neighborhood invalidation in the derived read index (pm-801d) — an event-sourced materialized view of the scorer inputs. Read-time work drops to combine-and-pack (4); rebuild-from-history stays the recovery path, preserving the derived-never-authoritative invariant. This is also the natural home for the per-author watermarks that pm-vvib candidates #4 novelty and #5 theory-of-mind derive — one fold pass maintains all of them."
  "2026-07-07T15:37:10.972Z",maintainer-agent,"Algorithm brainstorm 2026-07-07 (planning pass, continuation of (1)-(6)):\n(7) Two-stage retrieval funnel with per-source candidate quotas — (1)-(6) specify how to SCORE and PACK, but at millions of items (pm-g2zz) the scorer must never see the whole workspace; the missing explicit piece is the recall stage of the classic recall-then-rank architecture. Candidate generation unions bounded top-k slates from independent cheap sources, each with its own quota: (a) ANN top-k from the hybrid semantic index, (b) n-hop graph expansion from focus/claims/plan steps (the seed set of (2)), (c) top-k by folded activation from the write-time view of (6) (a simple sorted structure makes this O(k)), (d) the agent's own WIP/claimed set and watermark-delta (novelty candidates), (e) exact lexical/field-predicate hits. Per-source quotas guarantee slate DIVERSITY structurally (no single degenerate signal floods the pool) and make cost independent of workspace size: scoring is O(sum of quotas), never O(items). Quotas scale with the token budget, which is how the same funnel serves a 3-item scratch workspace (every source returns everything, union is the whole workspace) and a decades-deep archive unchanged — the spectrum invariant. Explainability extends naturally: --explain-ranking reports which source(s) recalled each candidate before the per-signal score breakdown. SDK-side behind scoreContextCandidates like (1)-(6); composes directly with (5) RRF, which can fuse the per-source ranks as its cold-start combiner."
  "2026-07-07T15:57:35.738Z",maintainer-agent,"Algorithm brainstorm 2026-07-07 (planning pass, continuation of (1)-(7)):\n(8) Sketch-backed scorer state for million-item scale — (6)'s write-time fold keeps per-item activation and per-author affinity counters, but at the pm-g2zz extreme (millions of items x thousands of concurrent authors) exact per-(author, item/tag) counter matrices become the new scale bottleneck: state grows O(authors x touched-items) and dominates the derived read index. Replace exact counters with probabilistic sketches, each with provable error bounds: (a) Count-Min sketch for author-affinity and tag/field co-occurrence counts (sub-linear memory, point-query overestimate bounded by epsilon*N with tunable width/depth); (b) HyperLogLog for distinct-cardinality signals (how many distinct authors/sessions touched this subtree — a trust/centrality input) at ~1.5KB per counter regardless of cardinality; (c) exponential-decay variants (time-decayed CM sketch) so ACT-R-style recency folding from (1) composes directly — decay applied at fold time, no rescan. Spectrum-neutral by construction: below a size threshold the fold stores EXACT counters and the sketch path is dormant; the switchover is an internal representation change invisible to --explain-ranking consumers (signal semantics identical, only precision epsilon differs, and the envelope can disclose 'approximate' when sketched). Derived-never-authoritative holds: sketches are read-index state, rebuildable from immutable history streams at any time; error compounds only within a rebuild epoch. Composes with (7)'s funnel — per-source top-k slates read sketch summaries, never raw streams — and with (5) RRF, which consumes ranks and is inherently robust to bounded count error. SDK-side behind scoreContextCandidates like (1)-(7)."
  "2026-07-07T16:35:16.531Z",maintainer-agent,"Algorithm brainstorm 2026-07-07 (planning pass, continuation of (1)-(8)):\n(9) Granularity-adaptive packing — coarse-to-fine representation selection under one token budget. (4) treats each candidate as an atomic (gain, cost) pair, but every item admits MULTIPLE representations with monotone cost/value: id-line (~10 tokens) < compact row (~25) < row+AC/deps (~80) < full body (~hundreds), and a PARENT chunk rollup can stand in for an entire sibling subtree (pm-vvib candidate (10) chunking). Formulate packing as a multiple-choice knapsack: for each candidate (or subtree) pick exactly ONE representation level or drop it. Per-level value curves are concave (diminishing returns per token), so the greedy density heuristic of (4) extends cleanly: start with every survivor at its cheapest level, compute marginal value-per-token for each LEVEL UPGRADE, and greedily buy upgrades until the budget is spent. Properties: (a) no cliff — an item that flat packing would cut entirely degrades to its id-line instead, so the agent at least knows it exists (the human gist-memory analog: recall THAT before recall WHAT); (b) chunk substitution is just another level priced at the subtree's rollup size, giving structure-aware compression for free; (c) explainability (3) is preserved — each served row can carry its level plus why it was not upgraded (budget exhausted vs low marginal density). Composes with the funnel (7): recall produces the slate, (1)-(5) value it, granularity packing spends the budget; rollup sizes/digests are maintained by the write-time fold (6) so packing stays read-cheap. Spectrum behavior: small workspaces have budget exceeding full-granularity cost, output identical to today; million-item workspaces emit a few full-detail items + chunk digests + an id-line gist tail, in O(slate x levels, log-factor for the upgrade heap) time."
  "2026-07-07T20:06:11.214Z",maintainer-agent,"Algorithm (10) structural fingerprints for analogical recall (Weisfeiler-Leman relational hashing). Serves pm-vvib candidate subsystem (11): retrieve past episodes whose relational SHAPE matches the current situation, independent of vocabulary. Index side: for every item, extract its typed local neighborhood (parent/child edges, dep kinds, status-transition sequence from history, close_reason class, link types) and run k rounds of WL label refinement — each round rehashes an item label with the multiset of its neighbors' labels, so after k rounds the label encodes the k-hop relational shape. The resulting multiset of subtree hashes is the item's structural fingerprint. Similarity = weighted Jaccard over fingerprints; MinHash + LSH banding gives sublinear candidate lookup, so analogical recall is one more bounded-quota source in the two-stage funnel (7), fused via RRF (5) with semantic and associative channels. Costs compose with the existing plan: fingerprints fold incrementally at write time (6) — a mutation re-refines only the k-hop neighborhood it touched; sketch-backed state (8) bounds index size at million-item scale; packing (4)/(9) treats a retrieved precedent as one candidate whose payload is the episode digest (resolution + top learning), never the raw subgraph. Explainability preserved (3): the matched WL subtree hashes decode to which relations aligned (\"both had a wontfix blocker feeding a release-gated dependent\"), rendered as one line in --explain-ranking. Spectrum behavior: small workspaces have few distinct shapes so candidates collapse into recency/semantic ranking (signal silent, zero cost); decades-scale workspaces get case-based precedent recall no content signal can produce. Distinct from (2) spreading activation (connectivity along EXPLICIT shared edges; this matches shape between DISCONNECTED regions) and from embedding similarity (content, not structure)."
  "2026-07-07T20:26:24.821Z",maintainer-agent,"Algorithm (11) open-loop tension scoring with decay floors (Zeigarnik persistence). Serves pm-vvib candidate subsystem (12): incomplete work must persist in assembled context until completed or deliberately parked, never fade under recency decay. Mechanism: maintain a per-agent open-loop registry — folded incrementally at write time (6) like all derived state — holding every loop the agent owns: claimed items, Decisions without recorded resolution, notes ending in unanswered questions, reviews awaiting reply. Each loop carries a tension score composed of deadline proximity, blocker fan-in (how many items the loop blocks — consumes the dep graph), decision-pending markers, and a claim-age shape that rises then plateaus, so ancient abandoned WIP hands off to stale-WIP hygiene (pm-w8q4) instead of dominating forever. Tension acts as a FLOOR under the salience scorer's decay term (1): an open loop's effective salience never drops below its tension, so it cannot be evicted by token-budget packing (4)/(9) while live. Release events — close, claim release, explicit parking (blocked-with-reason) — zero the floor and return the item to ordinary consolidation-managed scoring; each release is itself an entry in the immutable history stream, so the registry rebuilds exactly from replay. Bounded by design: the registry is capped per agent at working-memory scale (~7 loops, composing with chunking (9): overflow loops collapse under their parent chunk), so cost is O(active agents), independent of workspace size; sketch-backed state (8) is unnecessary here because the set is intrinsically small. Explainability (3): floored items render one line in --explain-ranking — held: open loop, claimed 3d ago, blocks 2, decision pending. Spectrum behavior: small workspaces never hit packing limits so the floor is a silent no-op; million-item thousand-agent workspaces guarantee every agent resumes with its own unfinished business first at zero scan cost. Distinct from (2) spreading activation (cue-driven associative boost; this is cue-INDEPENDENT persistence) and from (7) funnel quotas (source selection before fusion; this is a rank floor after fusion)."
  "2026-07-08T04:50:57.291Z",maintainer-agent,"Algorithm (12) co-change coupling mining + outcome-conditioned precedent projection (episodic future thinking; serves pm-vvib candidate 13). Two composable parts. Part A — evolutionary coupling from episodic streams: mine 'items/files that change together' association statistics directly from the immutable history (mining-software-repositories co-change coupling): for item pairs (i,j), maintain support = |sessions touching both| and confidence(i→j) = support / |sessions touching i|, where a 'session' is a same-author time-windowed burst of mutations (or an explicit focus session). Computed as a WRITE-TIME FOLD (algorithm 6) into a count-min-sketch-backed pair table (algorithm 8) so cost is O(burst width) per mutation and storage stays sublinear at millions of items; decay counts with ACT-R log-time activation (algorithm 1) so decades-old coupling fades without a cliff. This yields the tracker's latent 'hidden dependency' graph — edges nobody declared but history proves, exactly the edges that predict surprise breakage. Part B — outcome-conditioned precedent projection: given a target item (about to be claimed / planned), retrieve top-k precedents by WL structural fingerprint (algorithm 10) UNIONED with top-k by co-change neighborhood overlap from Part A, then score each precedent by outcome relevance: divergence signals from its close record (expected_result vs actual_result mismatch, reopen events, close_reason class, time-to-close vs estimate from pm-3hps calibration data). Emit (a) predicted blast radius = co-change neighbors above a confidence floor that are NOT in the declared dep/parent/file neighborhood (candidate advisory edges, feeding the pm-4ri6 dedupe/advisory surface), and (b) top failure precedents with one-line 'how it actually ended' summaries for the pm context / pm plan pre-mortem block. Both parts are recall-stage sources for the two-stage funnel (algorithm 7, new quota source) and their contributions stay linear/explainable in the scorer (algorithm 3). Spectrum-invariant: sketch + log decay for the millions-of-items end (pm-g2zz), degenerates gracefully to exact small tables under the pm-z436 small-end profile."
  "2026-07-08T04:59:00.593Z",maintainer-agent,"Algorithm (13) salience-gated broadcast arbitration with habituation (global-workspace competition; serves pm-vvib candidate 14). Purpose: in a workspace with thousands of concurrent agents, decide WHICH few events earn workspace-wide attention and for HOW LONG, without a daemon and without flooding every context envelope. Mechanism, three stages. Stage 1 — local salience scoring at write time: every mutation event already folds derived state (algorithm 6); the same fold computes a broadcast score as an explainable linear combination (algorithm 3) of: surprise (inverse of the event's predicted probability given co-change statistics, algorithm 12 Part A — an edit nobody's coupling history predicted scores high), blast radius (count of items/agents whose open loops (11) or claimed WIP sit inside the event's co-change + dep neighborhood), outcome severity (negativity-weighted: failure/wontfix/regression close-reasons outrank routine closes, pm-vvib candidate 7), and deadline pressure (proximity of release-gated dependents). Stage 2 — bounded workspace arbitration: a fixed-capacity broadcast set (~4 slots, human working-memory scale) maintained as a fold over the event stream (pm-e200 substrate, ADR pm-i7i4 no-daemon: arbitration re-evaluates lazily whenever any agent next assembles context); an event enters only by exceeding the weakest incumbent, and incumbents decay by ACT-R log-time activation (1) so the channel self-clears. Stage 3 — habituation / inhibition-of-return: repeated structurally similar events (same WL fingerprint class, algorithm 10) attenuate geometrically so one flaky gate cannot monopolize a slot, and an agent's acknowledgment (an ordinary immutable history event) suppresses re-serving THAT event to THAT agent while leaving it live for others — per-agent delivery state is derivable from each agent's own episodic stream, zero new authoritative state. Costs: O(1) score per mutation amortized via the existing fold; arbitration is O(slots) per context assembly; sketch-backed fingerprint classes (8) bound habituation memory at million-item scale. Explainability (3): each broadcast slot renders one line with its winning terms (\"broadcast: wontfix close blocks 3 release-gated items, 2 agents in radius\"). Spectrum behavior: single-agent or low-traffic workspaces never fill slot 1 above threshold — the block is absent and costs nothing; thousand-agent workspaces get coherent shared attention (no duplicated discovery, no missed cross-lane hazards) for ~4 lines of tokens per envelope. Distinct from (2) spreading activation (cue-driven, per-focus recall boost; this is cue-independent workspace-wide push), from (11) open-loop floors (persistence of MY unfinished work; this is arbitration among EVERYONE's events), and from the retrieval funnel (7) quotas (which select candidate items per source; this selects events for a dedicated always-on attention block)."
  "2026-07-08T22:51:13.305Z",maintainer-agent,"Planning pass 2026-07-08 (third follow-up): Algorithm (14) retrieval-conditioned contradiction gating for memory reconsolidation (serves pm-vvib candidate 15). Purpose: decide WHEN a retrieved precedent becomes eligible for an append-only correction delta, so the corpus self-corrects under use without thrashing on every read. Mechanism, three stages. Stage 1 — retrieval events as cheap immutable facts: whenever context assembly (algorithm 7 funnel) serves a precedent item into an agent's envelope, fold a (retriever, precedent_id, ts) retrieval event into sketch state (algorithm 8) — O(1), no daemon, replayable from the streams. Stage 2 — contradiction scoring at the NEXT write: when the retrieving agent later records an outcome on its own item (close with resolution/expected/actual, a learning, a decision), compute an explainable linear contradiction score (algorithm 3 weights) between that outcome and each recently-retrieved precedent: (a) outcome divergence — precedent's recorded resolution vs the new expected-vs-actual pair (categorical mismatch = strong signal); (b) estimate divergence — |log(actual_minutes/estimated_minutes)| of the new work when the precedent supplied the estimate prior; (c) semantic opposition — embedding distance flip between precedent decision text and the new learning text (reuses the existing vector index, no new store); (d) structural relevance gate — WL fingerprint similarity (algorithm 10) between the two work contexts, so only contradictions in STRUCTURALLY SIMILAR situations count (a divergent outcome in an unrelated context is noise, not correction pressure). Eligibility opens only when score crosses a threshold AND the habituation guard passes: per (retriever, precedent) pair at most one open window per K retrievals, mirroring the biological constraint that reconsolidation needs a labile window, not constant rewriting. Stage 3 — correction pressure as a fold-time retrieval signal: accepted deltas append as ordinary immutable events pairing (precedent_id, retrieving_context_id, correction); write-time maintenance (algorithm 6) folds a decaying correction-pressure counter per precedent that (i) demotes the precedent's retrieval rank proportionally, floored so originals never disappear (immutability + auditability), and (ii) attaches the N most recent corrections whenever the precedent IS served (candidate 15 acceptance shape). Confirmations (retrievals followed by consistent outcomes) fold the opposite way and harden rank — spaced retrieval-practice strengthening (pm-uwfs territory) composes here rather than duplicating. Spectrum behavior: small workspaces rarely cross threshold, cost is one sketch fold per retrieval; million-item workspaces get a queryable relitigation surface — precedents with sustained correction pressure are exactly the decisions the organisation keeps re-arguing, surfaced via ordinary list/search over folded metadata rather than a batch job."
body: "pm context and pm next currently assemble their working set from structural rules (dependency-aware actionability per ADR pm-9x6x: ready = active leaf with no open blocked_by, ordered by compareCriticalItems). That is correct but shallow: it uses only a fraction of the data the tracker already records, and it does not adapt between a 10-item hobby workspace and a million-item, decades-spanning one.\n\nProposal: a pluggable relevance-scoring engine (SDK-first) that ranks candidate items for context assembly by combining ALL available signals:\n- recency and activity density from the per-item history streams (recently touched, recently discussed, aging-WIP)\n- dependency-graph proximity to the agent's focus item, active claims, and current plan steps\n- structural priority signals: priority, risk, severity, deadline pressure, sprint/release membership\n- semantic similarity between the agent's focus/query and item corpus (reusing the existing hybrid search providers)\n- knowledge density: items carrying learnings/decisions relevant to the working set get surfaced so past lessons are re-injected instead of re-learned\n- author affinity: what this agent (PM_AUTHOR) touched before\n\nDesign constraints:\n- Scoring lives in the SDK as a documented, replaceable interface (scoreContextCandidates); the built-in scorer is just the default implementation — projects can ship their own via extensions.\n- Deterministic and explainable: --explain-ranking (or a score breakdown in json output) shows per-signal contributions, so agents and humans can audit why an item was surfaced.\n- Token-budgeted assembly: given a budget (explicit flag or config default), the engine packs the highest-value items and degrades gracefully (tighter projections before dropping items).\n- O(result) at scale: signal inputs must come from the derived read index (pm-801d) and search index, never a full workspace scan; benchmark on the pm-mi2x synthetic workspaces.\n- Small-workspace neutrality: on tiny workspaces the ranking must reduce to today's sensible ordering with zero configuration.\n\nThis is the core of the 'project management = context management' philosophy: the optimal context at any time, computed from all data, metadata, and history the workspace already has."
